noun.description: The material produced from a mill before sorting, especially the saleable output of a sawmill. In extended use: a person or thing regarded as average or mediocre.

adjective.description: Designating material produced from a mill before sorting, especially the saleable output of a sawmill. In extended use: lacking unusual or distinctive aspects; average, mundane, mediocre.

origin: Mid 17th century (in an earlier sense). From mill + run.
